    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="365"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.51G31/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1941—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>847. With reference to the provisions of our Trade Agreement with France<note
                        n="29" xml:id="d365fn1">Signed May 6, 1936, Executive Agreement Series No.
                        146, or 53 Stat. 2236.</note> applicable to Indochina, you should address a
                    note of protest to the appropriate French authorities in regard to the
                    preferential treatment accorded to Japanese products enumerated in list A,
                    annexed to the Indochinese-Japanese customs agreement of May 6, and make formal
                    reservation of American rights. A similar instruction has been sent to
                    Saigon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
